# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LeadIntel — environment variables
#
# The demo runs entirely on the in-browser MSW mock (no backend needed), so
# NONE of these are required to run `npm run dev`. They configure the optional
# production paths. Never commit real values — this file is an example only.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Public Supabase config (safe to expose; hardcoded fallbacks exist in code).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR_ANON_KEY

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bookings module (Cal.com) — SERVER-SIDE ONLY (Vercel serverless functions).
# These are secrets: they must never appear in the frontend bundle or be
# prefixed with VITE_. They are read only by api/bookings/* on the server.
#
# Booking happens via the embedded Cal.com widget. Freshness comes from Cal.com
# webhooks (instant) with polling as a fallback.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CAL_API_BASE=https://api.cal.com/v2
CAL_API_VERSION=2024-08-13                 # Cal.com bookings API version

# One block per AE (closer). Pick a short id for each AE (e.g. "hamna") — it
# becomes the suffix of every var. The _EMAIL must be the closer's LOGIN email:
# that's how a logged-in closer is matched to their Cal.com account + API key.
# A user-scoped Cal.com API key only returns that user's own bookings.
# CAL_API_KEY__HAMNA=<cal.com api key>               # secret
# CAL_AE_HAMNA_NAME=Hamna
# CAL_AE_HAMNA_URL=https://cal.com/hamna/30min
# CAL_AE_HAMNA_EMAIL=hamna@yourcompany.com
# CAL_API_KEY__SHAYAN=<cal.com api key>              # secret
# CAL_AE_SHAYAN_NAME=Shayan
# CAL_AE_SHAYAN_URL=https://cal.com/shayan/30min
# CAL_AE_SHAYAN_EMAIL=shayan@yourcompany.com

# Webhook receiver auth. Set this, then add ?token=<same value> to the webhook
# URL you register in Cal.com so only Cal.com can ping the endpoint.
# CAL_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<random_string>

# Lets the proxy join bookings to CRM leads AND lets the webhook push instant
# "changed" pings to the browser via Supabase Realtime. Without these the module
# still works (polling keeps the list fresh; leads just won't auto-attach).
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role_key>   # secret — server only
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon_key>                   # used for the realtime broadcast if no service key
